application.models

Class Booking

  • java.lang.Object
    • application.models.SuperModel
      • application.models.Booking

  • public class Booking
extends SuperModel
    Purpose:
    Booking class containing fields and methods pertaining to
    a single booking
    Description:
    Contains information about the booking in the form of String fields,
    and a list of seats for the Booking (note: unlike the one in Screening,
    the seats list in Booking does not contain information about any
    unbooked seats; there are no false values in the HashMap
    Version:
    $Date: 2017/12/14 16:00:00 $
    Author:
    Zaid Al Lahham and Aleksi Anttila

    • Constructor Detail

      • Booking

        public Booking(java.lang.String filmTitle,
               java.time.LocalDateTime dateTime,
               java.lang.String username,
               java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Boolean> seats)
        Constructor Sets the Booking's film title, dateTime, seats, and username of the Customer that made the Booking from the parameters; constructs a bookingID from the dateTime and the username.
        Parameters:
        filmTitle - Film title String to be set
        dateTime - LocalDateTime to be set
        username - Customer's username to be set
        seats - A HashMap; the key is a letter followed by a number (in the current version, "a1" to "d6"), and the value is always true; unbooked seats are not included here

      • Booking

        public Booking(org.json.JSONObject bookingJSON)
        Constructor Given a JSONObject, sets the fields of the Booking object based on the corresponding key-value pairs in the JSONObject; parses the JSONObject and calls the constructor above.
        Parameters:
        bookingJSON - JSONObject for the booking containing the following keys: filmTitle, dateTime, username, seats; the seats object should consist of key(String)-value(boolean) pairs in the same fashion as the seats field
